# Common Phone & Tablet Issues – Self-Help Knowledge Base

Purpose:  
Provide Cali AI with safe, simple troubleshooting guidance to help customers resolve common phone and tablet issues themselves, reducing unnecessary calls and store visits.

Applies to:  
iPhone, Android phones, iPads, Android tablets

---

## Battery & Power Issues

### Battery draining quickly
Common causes:
- Background apps
- High screen brightness
- Poor signal
- Degraded battery health

Suggested self-fixes:
- Restart the device
- Reduce screen brightness
- Enable Low Power / Battery Saver mode
- Check battery usage in settings and close heavy apps
- Update to the latest software version

Escalate to store if:
- Battery health is low
- Device shuts down suddenly or at high percentages

---

### Device won’t turn on
Common causes:
- Fully discharged battery
- Frozen software
- Faulty charger or cable

Suggested self-fixes:
- Charge for at least 30 minutes
- Try a different charging cable and plug
- Perform a force restart (device specific)
- Connect to a computer and wait

Escalate to store if:
- No response after charging and force restart
- Device becomes hot or smells unusual

---

### Device turns off randomly
Common causes:
- Battery degradation
- Software bugs
- Cold temperatures

Suggested self-fixes:
- Update software
- Check battery health in settings
- Avoid cold environments

Escalate to store if:
- Happens frequently or below 30–40% battery

---

## Screen & Display Issues

### Screen unresponsive or laggy
Common causes:
- Software glitch
- Screen protector interference
- Moisture on screen

Suggested self-fixes:
- Restart device
- Remove screen protector
- Clean screen with a dry cloth

Escalate to store if:
- Touch dead zones
- Screen does not respond at all

---

### Screen flickering or dim
Common causes:
- Auto-brightness bugs
- Display hardware issues

Suggested self-fixes:
- Disable auto-brightness
- Restart device
- Update software

Escalate to store if:
- Flickering continues or worsens

---

## Sound Issues

### Can’t hear calls or speaker sounds muffled
Common causes:
- Blocked speaker mesh
- Dust or debris
- Bluetooth routing audio elsewhere

Suggested self-fixes:
- Gently clean speaker mesh
- Turn off Bluetooth
- Restart device

Escalate to store if:
- Sound is distorted or silent

---

### Microphone not working
Common causes:
- Blocked microphone holes
- App permission issues

Suggested self-fixes:
- Clean mic openings gently
- Check microphone permissions for the app
- Test using a voice recorder

Escalate to store if:
- No sound is recorded at all

---

## Connectivity Issues

### Poor signal or no service
Common causes:
- Network outages
- SIM card issues
- Software bugs

Suggested self-fixes:
- Toggle Airplane Mode on and off
- Restart device
- Remove and reinsert SIM card
- Reset network settings

Escalate to store if:
- No signal with a known-working SIM

---

### Wi-Fi or Bluetooth not working
Common causes:
- Software glitches
- Router interference

Suggested self-fixes:
- Restart device
- Forget and reconnect to network
- Restart router
- Reset network settings

Escalate to store if:
- Wi-Fi or Bluetooth toggle is missing or greyed out

---

## Camera Issues

### Camera blurry or won’t focus
Common causes:
- Dirty lens
- Smudged camera protector
- Software glitches

Suggested self-fixes:
- Clean camera lens gently
- Remove camera protector
- Restart device

Escalate to store if:
- Camera shakes, shows black screen, or never focuses

---

### Camera app crashes
Common causes:
- Software corruption
- Low storage space

Suggested self-fixes:
- Restart device
- Update software
- Free up storage space

Escalate to store if:
- Crashes persist after restart and updates

---

## Software & Performance Issues

### Device running slow
Common causes:
- Full storage
- Too many background apps
- Outdated software

Suggested self-fixes:
- Restart device
- Delete unused apps and files
- Update software

Escalate to store if:
- Device freezes regularly

---

### Apps crashing repeatedly
Common causes:
- Outdated apps
- Corrupt app data

Suggested self-fixes:
- Update apps
- Reinstall affected apps
- Restart device

Escalate to store if:
- Multiple apps crash frequently

---

### Storage full
Common causes:
- Photos and videos
- Messaging app media
- App cache

Suggested self-fixes:
- Delete unused apps
- Back up photos to cloud storage
- Clear large message attachments

Escalate to store if:
- Storage does not free up after cleanup

---

## Charging Issues

### Device not charging properly
Common causes:
- Dirty charging port
- Faulty cable
- Weak power source

Suggested self-fixes:
- Try a different cable and plug
- Restart device
- Visually inspect port (no tools)

Escalate to store if:
- Cable won’t insert properly
- Charging cuts in and out

---

### Device charging slowly
Common causes:
- Low-power charger
- Background apps
- Battery health issues

Suggested self-fixes:
- Use the correct charger
- Close background apps
- Enable Low Power mode

Escalate to store if:
- Charging remains unusually slow

---

## Water & Physical Damage

### Device exposed to liquid
Immediate advice:
- Power off device immediately
- Do not charge
- Dry the exterior gently

Important rules:
- Never suggest rice
- Never suggest heat or hairdryers

Always escalate to store for:
- Any liquid exposure

---

### Dropped device or cracked screen
Suggested self-fixes:
- None

Escalate to store if:
- Cracks spreading
- Touch or display affected
- Sharp glass exposed

---

## Security & Access Issues

### Forgotten passcode
Suggested self-fixes:
- Use official account recovery methods

Escalate to store if:
- Customer needs help understanding reset options

---

### Face ID or fingerprint not working
Common causes:
- Dirty sensors
- Software glitches

Suggested self-fixes:
- Clean sensors
- Re-enrol biometrics
- Restart device

Escalate to store if:
- Biometric hardware not detected

---

## Global Safety Rules for AI

The AI must never:
- Suggest opening the device
- Suggest metal tools
- Suggest heat or rice
- Suggest charging after liquid exposure

Always escalate:
- Liquid damage
- Battery swelling
- Overheating
- Burning smells
- Safety concerns

---

## Default AI Framing

Recommended phrasing:
“If you’d like, I can guide you through a few quick checks that often fix this without needing a store visit.”

---

## When to Recommend a Store Visit
- Liquid exposure
- Physical damage
- Battery swelling
- No power after charging
- Repeated crashes after resets
- Any safety-related concern
